  "narrative": "DCF model for PROJECT-ATLAS as of 2026-07-15 (USD millions), mid-year convention. WACC of 8.61%% is built from a CAPM cost of equity and an after-tax cost of debt at the stated target weights. A five-year unlevered FCF forecast is driven by explicit revenue-growth, EBIT-margin, tax, D&A, capex, and working-capital assumptions, each carried in the assumptions register with a provenance tag and citation. The base case discounts to an enterprise value of 3,363.9, which walks down the enterprise-to-equity bridge (less debt and minority interest, plus cash and associates) to an equity value of 3,233.9, or about 26.95 per share on 120.0 shares. The upside and downside cases flex growth and margin per the documented scenario adjustments and bracket the base case. All scenario tie-outs pass and enterprise values are monotonic across the three cases. These figures are model outputs conditional on the stated assumptions; a qualified human must review the assumptions and cross-check against comparable-company and precedent-transaction analysis before any use. Illustrative valuation model for analytical purposes only; not investment advice, not a recommendation to buy, sell, or hold any security, not a price target, and not a fairness opinion. Outputs depend entirely on the stated assumptions, which a qualified human must review."
